        <abstract> 
<p>Asks CD for reference to the edition of <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi> that contains the original of Ernst Krause’s article on Dr Erasmus Darwin. There are serious differences between the translation by W. S. Dallas and the Feb [1879] article by Krause on which CD, in the preface to <hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi>, says it was based. SB notes in particular that the concluding sentence of the translation, which is clearly aimed at [SB’s] <hi rend="italic">Evolution, old and new</hi>, is not in the original. Since readers will assume the text of <hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi> was written before his book appeared, SB asks for an explanation.</p> 
        </abstract>
